7 PLANNED CHANGES TO IMPROVE SAFETY 

CRNF is continuously investigating and reviewing technology and/or applications that could possibly enhance its safety efforts. These currently include:
-- Completed evaluation of an alternative chemical for chlorine which resulted in chlorine being removed from the plant;
-- Enhanced training in incident investigation methods for identified personnel;
-- Implementation of a Safety Suggestion Policy for use by all employees for improving safety in the work areas;
-- Expanded emergency drills for ammonia.
